<topic id="syntax-highlight-and-content-completion">
  <title>Syntax Highlighting in XQuery</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>XQuery<indexterm>Syntax highlighting</indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p conkeyref="reusables-editing-documents/syntax-highlight-p" id="p_ajd_cgk_54b"/>
    <p id="p_bjd_cgk_54b">To customize the colors or styles used for the syntax highlighting colors for XQuery files,
      follow these steps:<ol id="ol_cjd_cgk_54b">
        <li id="li_djd_cgk_54b" irina="irina"><ph conkeyref="reusables-preferences-pages/Open-the-preferences-page"/>.</li>
        <li id="li_ejd_cgk_54b" irina="irina">Go to <xref href="preferences-colors-sh.dita#preferences-colors-sh"><menucascade>
              <uicontrol>Editor</uicontrol>
              <uicontrol>Syntax Highlight</uicontrol>
            </menucascade></xref>.</li>
        <li id="li_fjd_cgk_54b" irina="irina">Select and expand the <uicontrol>XQuery/XPath</uicontrol> section in the top pane.</li>
        <li id="li_gjd_cgk_54b" irina="irina">Select the component you want to change and customize the colors or styles using the
          selectors to the right of the pane.</li>
      </ol></p>
    <p id="p_hjd_cgk_54b">You can see the effects of your changes in the <uicontrol>Preview</uicontrol> pane.</p>
  </body>
